{{Expand Hungarian|Szamosközy István|date=September 2010}} '''Stefan Zamosius (Szamosközy)''' (1570–1612) was a [[Hungary|Hungarian]] [[Renaissance Humanism|humanist]] and [[historian]].
==Life== Szamosközy was born in Kolozsvár, [[Principality of Transylvania (1570–1711)|Transylvania]] (now [[Cluj-Napoca]], [[Romania]]) to a [[Calvinist]] family. He completed his studies at [[Heidelberg]] and [[Padova]]<!-- in which year? -->. In 1593 he returned to Transylvania and started to work at [[Alba Iulia|Gyulafehérvár]] for the archive of the Transylvanian court. There he started collecting materials and writing his major work on [[History of Hungary|Hungarian history]].
[[Stephen Bocskai]] nominated him as the official court historian.
==Works== * In Padova he published a Collection of [[Ancient Rome|Roman]] inscriptions in [[Dacia]] * he published also a numismatic treatise
His unfinished Hungarian history was never published but parts are extant in many manuscript copies. [[Farkas Bethlen (1639–1679)|Farkas Bethlen]] saved longer parts in his Transylvanian history. He designed his work based on the example of [[Antonio Bonfini]]'s Decades (Tenths). [[Sándor Szilágyi]] published Szamosközy's works in four volumes in ''Szamosközy történeti maradványai'', Budapest 1876–1880.
* Hebdomanes (Sevenths) * Pentates (Fifths)[http://www.antikvarium.hu/ant/book.php?func=gyorsszerzo&tipus=tema&kezdet=1&darab=50&talalat=15&rendezes=Cim_AZ&temakorID=0&sszam=2&ID=10069] * History of the year 1594 * Analecta lapidum vetustorum et nonnullarum in Dacia antiquitatum[https://books.google.ro/books?id=GAM6AAAAcAAJ&printsec=frontcover&hl=ro&source=gbs_ge_summary_r#v=onepage&q&f=false]
==Literature== * {{Cite book| last=Szamosközy | first=I. | title=History of Transylvania (Hungarian: Erdely Törtenéte) | location=Budapest | year=1963}} [http://www.antikvarium.hu/ant/book.php?func=gyorsszerzo&tipus=tema&kezdet=1&darab=50&talalat=15&rendezes=Cim_AZ&temakorID=0&sszam=2&ID=10069] * {{Cite book| editor=Kulcsár Péter | title=Humanist Historians (Hungarian: Humanista Történetírók) | publisher=Szépirodalmi Könyvkiadó | year=1977 | location=Budapest}}
