'''Mirosław Golon''' (born 1964) is a Polish historian. Professor of [[Nicolaus Copernicus University in Toruń]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://wyborcza.pl/1,91250,5333802,Cenckiewicz_walczy_z_grzechem.html|title=Cenckiewicz walczy z grzechem|last=Daszczyński|first=Roman|date=21 June 2008|work=[[Gazeta Wyborcza]]|language=Polish|accessdate=15 April 2011}}</ref> member of [[Institute of National Remembrance]], [[Polish Historical Society (Polish)|Polish Historical Society]] and [[Toruń Scientific Society]].

Author of over 90 publications, his research interests center on the [[history of Poland]] during [[Stalinist]] period (1945–1956), Polish-Soviet relations of that period, history of minorities in Poland in the 20th century and [[history of Pomerania]].

